<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// SmallSet - This maintains a set of unique values, optimizing for the case</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// when the set is small (less than N).  In this case, the set can be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// maintained with no mallocs.  If the set gets large, we expand to using an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="130"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// std::set to maintain reasonable lookup times.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="131"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> T, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> N, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> C = std::less&lt;T&gt;&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallset"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallset/#a642ef3f957486e94785fdc2ccafcb692">SmallSet</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Use a SmallVector to hold the elements here (even though it will never</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// reach its &#39;large&#39; stage) to avoid calling the default ctors of elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// we will never use.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;T, N&gt;</a> Vector;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><span class="doxyHighlight">  std::set&lt;T, C&gt; Set;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In small mode SmallPtrSet uses linear search for the elements, so it is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="140"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// not a good idea to choose this value too high. You may consider using a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="141"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// DenseSet&lt;&gt; instead if you expect many elements in the set.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="142"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;assert</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/regcomp-c/#a0240ac851181b84ac374872dc5434ee4">N</a> &lt;= 32, </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;N should be small&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="143"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Returns a pair. The first value of it is an iterator to the inserted</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Equality comparison for SmallSet.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Iterates over elements of LHS confirming that each element is also a member</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="272"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// of RHS, and that RHS contains no additional values.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Equivalent to N calls to RHS.count.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// For small-set mode amortized complexity is O(N^2)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00275" /><CodeLine lineNumber="275"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// For large-set mode amortized complexity is linear, worst case is O(N^2) (if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00276" /><CodeLine lineNumber="276"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// every hash collides).</span></CodeLine>
